7 June 2017The African National Congress congratulates its National Executive Committee member, Comrade Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma, for being honoured with the Lifetime Achievement Award at the Africa Energy Forum (AEF) which is currently underway in Copenhagen, Denmark.Comrade Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma, former Chairperson of the African Union Commission, has been honoured for her indisputable role in the upliftment and empowerment of women across the African Continent.The Africa Energy Forum, hosted annually, is an international investment meeting for Africa's power, energy, infrastructure and industrial sectors. It brings together representatives from governments and utilities across the continent and the World at large to identify opportunities in the industry and to form partnerships in order to progressively advance the industry.As the ANC, we extend our compliments to Comrade Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma for her progressive role in the continent, which elevates South Africa, and the continent at large, to higher standards in terms of uplifting and empowering women.Issued by the African National CongressEnquiries Zizi Kodwa 082 330 4910 National SpokespersonKhusela Sangoni 072 854 5707 National Communications Manager